WEBVTT

00:11.408 --> 00:14.410
Okay. You want to live with me,
you eat when I eat.

00:14.411 --> 00:16.512
Man, afterwards, we can get
some leftovers, go home

00:16.513 --> 00:19.582
and watch this documentary
on the '70s gas crisis.

00:19.583 --> 00:21.350
Wait. Didn't we just watch that?

00:21.351 --> 00:23.753
No, no, no, man,
that was a documentary

00:23.754 --> 00:26.255
on the '70s calculator craze.
That was a game changer.

00:26.256 --> 00:28.557
Americans didn't have
to use their brains anymore.

00:28.558 --> 00:32.228
Well, actually, I got a date tonight.

00:32.875 --> 00:35.185
Oh. Well, go ahead, invite her by.

00:35.186 --> 00:36.968
Matter of fact,
why don't you call up Rel?

00:36.969 --> 00:38.160
Everybody can come by.

00:38.161 --> 00:40.863
We do not get together enough
as a family, man.

00:40.864 --> 00:43.132
Dad, we just watched
the Bulls game two nights ago.

00:43.133 --> 00:44.767
You're gonna miss these
moments when I'm gone.

00:44.768 --> 00:46.669
I'll be out the house,
walking around naked,

00:46.670 --> 00:49.138
don't even know my own name,
can't find my way back home.

00:49.139 --> 00:51.807
Hey, here comes the chef. Cool.

00:55.045 --> 00:57.212
Konnichiwa.

01:05.622 --> 01:07.957
All right, we're gonna start
with the vegetables, okay?

01:07.958 --> 01:09.892
Look at these vegetables...
Oh, look at that.

01:09.893 --> 01:11.594
Oh, look at that.

01:11.595 --> 01:13.835
Choo-choo! Chooga-chugga,
chugga-chugga, chugga-chugga...

01:15.031 --> 01:17.500
Oh, and I'm about... and I'm
gonna throw it over there.

01:17.501 --> 01:19.501
You ready? Here we go.

01:24.307 --> 01:27.176
Uh...

01:27.177 --> 01:30.379
Give me... give me,
give me one second.

01:32.682 --> 01:34.483
Damn it, Harold!

01:34.484 --> 01:37.453
What is wrong with you?!
Okay, it's just a shrimp tail!

01:37.454 --> 01:40.322
It should be thrown in the bowl!
Why did you use your left hand?

01:40.323 --> 01:42.157
You're right-handed! Also,

01:42.158 --> 01:44.326
you're not supposed
to use the Japanese accent.

01:44.327 --> 01:46.595
They've told you a hundred times
that it's racist,

01:46.596 --> 01:49.164
and it makes everybody at work
feel uncomfortable.

01:49.165 --> 01:51.433
You don't want them
to start talking jive, do you?

01:51.434 --> 01:53.469
Do you?!

01:56.940 --> 01:59.608
Ah, there. You know what I mean?

01:59.609 --> 02:01.544
All right, what are we gonna do?

02:01.545 --> 02:03.012
We're gonna get these eggs
going, right?

02:03.013 --> 02:05.881
Oh. Egg time.

02:05.882 --> 02:08.383
Egg time. Ooh!

02:08.384 --> 02:10.386
Aah!

02:16.760 --> 02:19.228
One second, I'll be right back.

02:20.797 --> 02:23.132
You idiot!

02:23.133 --> 02:25.134
You don't know
how to break a freaking egg?!

02:25.135 --> 02:27.236
Now you got yolk on your hand!

02:27.237 --> 02:28.904
Damn it! Stop it, Harold!

02:33.810 --> 02:35.477
Uh, hi.

02:35.478 --> 02:37.947
You know, this...

02:37.948 --> 02:40.282
Look, guys, I'll-I'll level with you.

02:40.283 --> 02:42.451
I don't have a Japanese accent.

02:42.452 --> 02:45.020
- I don't know if you knew that.
- Yeah.

02:45.021 --> 02:48.090
I'm an ordinary African-American
man named Harold.

02:48.091 --> 02:51.226
Guys, look, this is my first day.

02:51.227 --> 02:53.429
I just really wanted
to impress you guys.

02:53.430 --> 02:55.431
I've been training all week, and,

02:55.432 --> 02:58.634
you know, my family's usually
disappointed!

02:58.635 --> 03:00.736
Why did you put your hands
on the grill, you idiot?!

